  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter, white sugar, and brown sugar until light and fluffy.",
    "Beat in the vanilla and eggs.",
    "In a separate bowl, combine the flour, baking soda, and salt.",
    "Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing until just combined.",
    "Stir in the chocolate chips.",
    "Drop spoonfuls of the dough onto a baking sheet, spacing them about 2 inches apart.",
    "Bake for 8-10 minutes or until the edges are golden brown.",
    "Allow the cookies to cool on the baking sheet for 5 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely."
